<section xmlns="http://xml.house.gov/schemas/uslm/1.0" xmlns:html="http://www.w3.org/1999/xhtml" style="-uslm-lc:I80" id="id80bace1d-3a70-11f1-b817-c08bf6d1fe2c" identifier="/us/usc/t40/s3505"><num value="3505">§ 3505.</num><heading> Forgiveness of outstanding advances</heading><content>
<p style="-uslm-lc:I11" class="indent0">In accordance with accounting and other procedures the Secretary of Housing and Urban Development prescribes, each advance made by the Secretary under this chapter that had any principal amount outstanding on <date date="1988-02-05">February 5, 1988</date>, was forgiven. The terms and conditions of any contract, or any amendment to a contract, for that advance with respect to any promise to repay the advance were canceled.</p>
</content><sourceCredit id="id80bace1e-3a70-11f1-b817-c08bf6d1fe2c">(<ref href="/us/pl/107/217">Pub. L. 107–217</ref>, <date date="2002-08-21">Aug. 21, 2002</date>, <ref href="/us/stat/116/1168">116 Stat. 1168</ref>.)</sourceCredit>
